## 🧩 Package-by-Package Breakdown

### 1. `extension/` — Chrome Extension (MV3)
The data entry point of the entire system.

- **`manifest.json`** — MV3, targets `axcl2s.dialerhosting.com/*/realtime_report.php*`, requests `storage`, `alarms`, `tabs`, `scripting`.
- **`background/service_worker.js`** — The beating heart. Uses `chrome.alarms` (1-min tick) to find Vicidial tabs, request scrapes, and POST snapshots to the gateway. Has a smart retry/inject logic when content scripts aren't ready. Tracks state (`scraperState`) in `chrome.storage`.
- **`content/content_script.js`** — The scraper. Parses the live Vicidial page DOM into a structured `snapshot` object containing: `summary` (tile KPIs), `meta` (dial level, dialable leads, dropped %, etc.), `agents[]` (with `stateBucket` from row color class), and `waitingCalls[]`. Uses `MutationObserver` for sub-second change detection + periodic heartbeat fallback. Throttled at 1.5s.
- **`shared/settings.js`** — Gateway URL, auth token, scrape config, runtime state — all persisted in `chrome.storage`. Has migration logic for backwards-compat.
- **`shared/parse.js`** — Pure utility: number parsing, dropped/answered splitting, `TR*` CSS class → state bucket mapping.
- **`popup/`** — Login UI + gateway status + last snapshot display.
- **`options/`** — Configure gateway URL + connection test.

**State Bucket Map (13 buckets):** `chatting`, `email`, `waiting_lt_1m`, `waiting_gt_1m`, `waiting_gt_5m`, `oncall_gt_10s`, `oncall_gt_1m`, `oncall_gt_5m`, `paused_gt_10s`, `paused_gt_1m`, `paused_gt_5m`, `threeway_gt_10s`, `deadcall`.

---

### 2. `live-gateway/` — Node.js Backend
**The central nervous system.** Express HTTP + WebSocket server.

**Stack:** `express`, `ws`, `jsonwebtoken`, `sql.js` (pure WASM SQLite — no native build tools needed on Windows), `dotenv`, `cors`.

**`src/server.js`** — Wires everything together:
- JWT-protected HTTP routes
- WebSocket at `/ws`
- Automatic shift report scheduler (env-driven: `REPORTS_AUTO=1`, `REPORTS_DAILY_AT_HHMM`)
- Slack alert fan-out on every snapshot ingest

**Routes:**
| Route | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `GET /api/health` | Liveness probe |
| `POST /api/auth/login` | JWT login (single admin user from env) |
| `POST /api/live/snapshot` | Extension ingest + alert detection |
| `GET /api/shift/summary` | Agent bucket rollups by hour |
| `GET /api/shift/intelligence` | First hour / half shift / full shift + yesterday compare |
| `GET /api/shift/callflow` | Call-flow hourly series + rollups + peak waiting hour |
| `GET/PUT /api/admin/settings` | Read/write gateway settings |
| `GET /api/alerts` | Alert history |
| `POST /api/alerts/:id/action` | Ack/resolve |
| `GET /api/reports` | List generated reports |
| `POST /api/reports/shift/generate` | Trigger HTML report generation |
| `GET /api/reports/:id/download` | Download report |
| `GET /api/intelligence/insights` | Computed insights (first hour rush, peak consistency, proactive staffing) |
| `POST /api/admin/notifications/slack/test` | Test Slack webhook |

**`src/db/core.js`** — Initializes `sql.js` SQLite with 8 tables:
- `app_settings` — Key/value store for shift config, retention, notifications, alerts thresholds
- `raw_snapshots` — Full JSON payloads, indexed by shift_date + hour
- `shift_buckets` — Per-hour, per-bucket agent count aggregates
- `callflow_snapshots` — Point-in-time call metrics
- `callflow_hourly` — Rolled-up avg/max per hour (active, waiting, ivr, ringing, dropped%)
- `generated_reports` — Report metadata index
- `alerts` — Alert records with status (open/acked/resolved)

Has **lightweight auto-migration** via `PRAGMA table_info()` for schema additions.

**Default settings:** Asia/Karachi timezone (UTC+5), shift 19:00→04:30, retention 14 days raw / 60 days buckets.

---

### 3. `dashboard/` — Web SPA (Vanilla JS, no bundler)
A **frameworkless** single-page app — no React, no Webpack, just ES modules opened directly in the browser.

**Pages (7):**
| Page | What it shows |
|---|---|
| **Overview** | Live KPI summary, meta (dial level, drop%), agent state buckets, live sparkline trends (active/waiting/purple) |
| **Shift Analytics** | DB-driven per-hour breakdown + call-flow chart + comparison to yesterday |
| **Intelligence** | First-hour rush analysis, peak-hour consistency (30-day window), proactive staffing recommendation |
| **Reports** | Generate/view/download printable HTML shift reports |
| **Alerts** | Anomaly feed with ack/resolve actions |
| **Settings** | Shift timezone, start/end time, retention, alert thresholds, Slack config, notification preferences |
| **Advanced** | Raw DB table explorer + safe clear with multi-step confirmation |

**Architecture highlights:**
- `appShell.js` is the app orchestrator — manages state, WS connection, page routing via URL hash, session persistence in `localStorage`
- `patchOverviewDom()` does **surgical DOM patching** on live snapshots (no full re-render, just `textContent` diffs)
- `recentPoints[]` stores an in-memory rolling buffer of 90 trend points for sparklines
- Toast notifications + audio beeps on alerts
- Hard-reload detection (warns if Live Server auto-refresh is firing)

---

### 4. `alerts/detector.js` — Real-time Anomaly Engine
Four alert types, each with **configurable thresholds, sustain windows, and per-shift cooldowns:**

| Alert Type | Trigger Condition |
|---|---|
| `waiting_spike` | `calls_waiting >= threshold` sustained for N seconds |
| `purple_overload` | `oncall_gt_5m agents >= threshold` sustained for N seconds |
| `drop_percent_jump` | `dropped%` jumps by N points in a single snapshot |
| `staffing_shortage` | `waiting - ready_agents >= gap` sustained, with **linear ETA forecast** |

Each alert includes **probable cause hints** (no ready agents, agents paused during spike, all busy, etc.) and a `details_json` with full context.

The **ETA forecast** uses linear regression over the last 10 minutes of the `waitingSeries` to predict when the waiting spike threshold will be hit.

---

### 5. `intelligence/insights.js` — Strategic Insights Engine
Three computed insights fed to the Intelligence page:

1. **First Hour Rush** — Compares volume in hours 0–1 vs shift average using `calls_today_max` delta.
2. **Peak Hour Consistency** — Looks back 30 days, finds which hour had the highest `calls_waiting_max` each day, and reports which hour is consistently the worst with a confidence %.
3. **Proactive Staffing** — Real-time queue risk (NORMAL/ELEVATED/HIGH) + suggested agent count + ETA to spike threshold using linear regression on recent callflow.

